 cover letter is a document that you submit with your resume when applying for a job. It's a personalized introduction to your resume that highlights your most relevant skills and experiences. 
Purpose 
Demonstrate your enthusiasm for the role
Show why you're a good fit for the company
Explain how your experience makes you qualified for the position
What to include
Opening paragraph: State your reason for writing, the position you're applying for, and how you heard about it 
Middle paragraphs: Explain why you're interested in the role and the company 
Closing paragraph: Reiterate your interest in the role and the company 
Tips 
Use specific examples from your experience to demonstrate your qualifications
Avoid overusing the word "I"
Don't repeat your entire resume
A cover letter is especially important for entry-level applicants who might not have much work experience to list on their resume. 
